<item>
            <title>[THRIFT-4421] golang tests rely on gomock, which has change behaviour, causing tests to fail</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/THRIFT-4421</link>
                <project id="12310800" key="THRIFT">Thrift</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;Golang gomock&apos;s Controller object no longer allows multiple invocations of Finish().  But the lib/go unit-tests use this idiom.  So change that (trivial).&lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment>&lt;p&gt;Ubuntu 16.04.3 amd64&lt;/p&gt;</environment>
        <key id="13124501">THRIFT-4421</key>
